suppose you have a method that returns a list.

List aList = getList();

then you want to typecast it into an ArrayList, you would type:

ArrayList anArrayList = (ArrayList)aList;

Now this would cause an error if the List you're trying to cast can't be turned into an ArrayList.

So the safer code would be:

if (aList instanceof ArrayList){
   ArrayList anArrayList = (ArrayList)aList;
}
else{
   // handle case where List isn't castable, print
   // a message or throw an exception, etc.
}

This way, you're sure you can cast it, and you have a place to handle what happens if you can't convert your list into an ArrayList. Are you going to abort the whole program, work without the list, try to convert the list into an ArrayList another way, etc.

