The key factors that affect FedEx services are as follows: 

1. the overall customer demand for various services 
2. the volumes of transportation and business services provided through our networks, primarily measured by average daily volume and shipment weight;
3. the mix of services purchased by customers;
4. the prices FedEx obtain for their services, primarily measured by average price per shipment (yield); and 
